PYTHON:
======
Scripting:
	it means writing some code and executing it by double-cliking the file
	example:
		#!/bin/python3 => tells linux how to execute this script
		print("hello! world")
socket MODULE:
	socket=> internal end-point to send or recieve data
	sock_stream when TCP
	sock_degram when UDP
	socket.AF_INET => ipv4
	socket.SOCK_STREAM => port
sample programe:
	import socket
	host = '127.0.0.1'
	port = 7777
	s = socket.socket(socket.AF_INET, socket.SOCK_STREAM)
	s.connect((host,port))